   "source": [
    "## Step 5: Calculate Cumulative Returns\n",
    "\n",
    "Cumulative return answers: *\"If I invested \\$1 at the start of the year, what is it worth today?\"*  \n",
    "\n",
    "The formula is: `(1 + daily_return).cumprod() - 1`  \n",
    "- We add 1 so we can multiply (compounding)\n",
    "- `cumprod()` multiplies all values up to each date\n",
    "- We subtract 1 at the end to get back to a percentage\n",
    "\n",
    "I was getting this error: `RuntimeWarning: overflow encountered in accumulate\n",
    "  return bound(*args, **kwds)`\n",
    "\n",
    "  So, I had to adjust the datatype in the first step based on what I read on Stack Overflow"
   ]
  },
