   "source": [
    "## Step 6: Build a Summary Statistics Table\n",
    "\n",
    "I still think of this step in terms of SQL — we're essentially doing a GROUP BY summary, but in Pandas.  \n",
    "\n",
    "We'll calculate:\n",
    "- **Total Return** — how much did it grow over the year?\n",
    "- **Avg Daily Return** — average day-over-day movement\n",
    "- **Volatility** — standard deviation of daily returns (how \"bumpy\" was the ride?)\n",
    "- **Sharpe-like Ratio** — return divided by risk (higher = better risk-adjusted performance)"
   ]
  },
